\details{
\strong{Scope.} For power analysis, study design, method comparison on planted patterns,
recovery / property tests, and replicating published designs. Not evidence of real-world
validity: simulated carelessness is more stylized than real, and a simulation-trained
advantage may not transfer (Schroeders et al. 2022). Anchor accuracy claims to labeled
real data.

\strong{Attentive model.} A graded response model: one factor per scale in \code{items}, default
loadings 0.7, identity factor correlations, latent traits from \code{trait_distribution}.
Reverse-keyed items load negatively, so the matrix is raw (as-clicked) and keying-sensitive
indices reverse-score internally from \code{items}. Thresholds come from \code{marginals} (presets or
probability vectors; default \code{"peaked"}, an as-clicked target) or raw \code{thresholds}
(mutually exclusive). Default loadings can leave synonym / antonym pairs below
\code{\link[=cier_psychsyn]{cier_psychsyn()}} / \code{\link[=cier_psychant]{cier_psychant()}}'s \code{critical_r}; raise \code{loadings} toward 0.8 or lower
\code{critical_r}.

