\code{extreme}, \code{diagonal} (with a bounce option), \code{alternating}, \code{markov}, and \code{speeder}
(attentive content but careless times); the default weights all equally. Per-style knobs
go in \code{pattern_params}, a named list of named knob lists (e.g.
\code{list(straightline = list(anchor = "value", value = 5))}). An unknown knob name is a typed
error; what is applied is recorded in \code{truth$params}. Accepted knobs:
\itemize{
\item \code{random}, \code{speeder}: none.
\item \code{straightline}: \code{anchor} (\code{"position"} or \code{"value"}, default \code{"position"}),
\code{q} (relative position 0..1), \code{value} (a whole number in every item's
range), \code{switch_prob} (0..1, default 0).
\item \code{midpoint}: \code{jitter} (non-negative whole number, default 0).
\item \code{extreme}: \code{p_high} (0..1, default 0.5).
\item \code{diagonal}: \code{step} (positive whole number, default 1), \code{start} (1..K_min),
\code{bounce} (logical, default \code{FALSE}).
\item \code{alternating}: \code{period} (whole \verb{>= 2}, default 2), \code{values} (positions in
1..K_min, \strong{not} raw response values), \code{start_offset} (0..\code{period} - 1).
\item \code{markov}: \code{transition} (a K_min x K_min row-stochastic matrix), \code{initial}
